<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" >
<head>
<title>BFG Tutorial Bin</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1" />
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="${application_url}/static/css/default.css" />
<!--[if IE 6]>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="$[application_url}/static/css/fix.css" type="text/css" />
<![endif]-->
</head>
<body>
<div id="container">
  <div id="header">
    <div id="title"><image class="bfglogo" src="${application_url}/static/images/site/raygun.png" height="60" /><span>B F G</span></div>
    <div id="navcontainer">
      <ul id="navlist">
        <li><a href="${application_url}">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="${application_url}/documentation">Documentation</a></li>
        <li id="active"><a href="${application_url}/community" id="current">Community</a></li>
        <li><a href="${application_url}/software">Software</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="slogan">
    <p>Gets you and your web applications up to speed. In a blast.</p>
  </div>
  <div id="content">

      <div id="subnav" tal:condition="tutorials">
        <div id="news">
          <div class="newsheader">Recent tutorials</div>
          <ul>
            <li tal:repeat="tutorial tutorials[:20]">
              <a href="${tutorial.url}">${tutorial.title}, by ${tutorial.author} on ${tutorial.date}</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

    <div id="one">

      <h1>BFG Tutorial Bin</h1>
      <div class="message" tal:condition="message|nothing"
           tal:content="message">Error message</div>

       <a href="${tutorialbin_url}add">Add tutorial</a>

      <div class="userinfo" tal:condition="user">
          You are currently logged in as <b>${user}</b>
          <a href="${application_url}/logout">Log Out</a>
      </div>

      <div class="left">
          <p>If you have a piece of code that you can share to enlighten the community, but don't have the time to write a long document, consider using our <a href="${tutorialbin_url}add">quick and dirty tutorial maker</a>. Just paste some code, add an explanatory text and a title and you're done.</p>
    
        <div tal:condition="latest">
        <style tal:content="style_defs"></style>
        <h2>${latest['title']}</h2>
          <span class="entryheader">Author:</span> ${latest['author_name']} <br/>
          <span class="entryheader">Date:</span> ${latest['date']} <br/>
          <span class="entryheader" tal:condition="latest['author_url']">External URL: <a href="${latest['author_url']}">${latest['author_url']}</a></span><br tal:condition="latest['author_url']"/>
          <div><pre>${latest['text']}</pre></div>
          <div>${latest['formatted_code']}</div>
       </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="footer">
    <div class="copy">Copyright &copy; 2009 | <a href="http://www.agendaless.com/">Agendaless and contributors</a></div>
    <div class="credit">Design based on a theme by <a href="http://realalibi.com">Robobuilder</a></div>
  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
